=== Example 013: Basic awk command ===
Using backticks to call awk (print all lines):
Alice 25 95.5
Bob 30 87.2
Charlie 35 92.8
Diana 28 88.9
Eve 32 91.3

awk print specific fields (print first and third field):
awk: cmd. line:1: {print , }
awk: cmd. line:1:        ^ syntax error

awk with field separator (print with comma separator):
,,
,,
,,
,,
,,

awk with conditions (print lines where age > 30):
awk: cmd. line:1:  > 30 {print , }
awk: cmd. line:1:  ^ syntax error

awk with calculations (print name and score*2):
awk: cmd. line:1: {print , *2}
awk: cmd. line:1:        ^ syntax error

awk with BEGIN and END:
Name	Age	Score
		
		
		
		
		
End of data

awk with variables (sum of scores):
awk: cmd. line:1: {sum += } END {print "Total score:", sum}
awk: cmd. line:1:         ^ syntax error

awk with string functions (uppercase names):
awk: cmd. line:1: {print toupper(), , }
awk: cmd. line:1:                ^ 0 is invalid as number of arguments for toupper

awk with pattern matching (names starting with A):
awk: cmd. line:1: /^A/ {print , , }
awk: cmd. line:1:             ^ syntax error

awk with multiple conditions (age > 30 AND score > 90):
awk: cmd. line:1:  > 30 &&  > 90 {print , , }
awk: cmd. line:1:  ^ syntax error

awk with formatting (printf):
awk: cmd. line:1: {printf "%-10s %3d %6.1f
awk: cmd. line:1:         ^ unterminated string

awk from stdin (echo | awk):
awk: cmd. line:1: {print , , }
awk: cmd. line:1:        ^ syntax error

awk with field width:
awk: cmd. line:1: {printf "%-15s %3d %6.1f
awk: cmd. line:1:         ^ unterminated string
